LOCAL MODE  (no PostgreSQL, no login needed)

  1. npm run use:local   <- one command: sets up SQLite DB,
                           disables auth, seeds admin account
  2. npm run dev         <- open http://localhost:3000/dashboard
     Go directly to /dashboard -- no login required

To restore production mode (PostgreSQL + login):
  npm run use:prod       <- one command restores everything


PRODUCTION MODE  (PostgreSQL + auth enabled)

  1. Set DATABASE_URL and AUTH_SECRET in .env
  2. npx prisma migrate dev --name init
  3. npm run db:seed     <- creates admin account
  4. npm run dev         <- open http://localhost:3000/login


